    <stitle>CAB: 7000 AND 8000 SERIES MODELS - ADJUSTMENTS - CAB DOOR</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x16029202" svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="0">
        <title>CAB DOOR</title>
        <para>When the door is properly adjusted, it should fit the opening with 1/4- to 5/16- inch (6- to 8- mm) space
            all around the door frame. A newspaper sheet should not be able to pass between the weather seal and door
            frame (paper should tear).
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Door weather seal should contact the door frame with slight pressure but without damage to
                the seal.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Door should latch, lock, and release without undue effort.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Door should not rattle when vehicle is moving.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
